# STOP — Do not edit Cursor plugin files in the installed mirror

The path `~/.cursor/plugins/local/<plugin-name>/...` is the **installed mirror** maintained by the Cursor plugin installer. It is **not** the plugin source repo. Edits applied there are lost on the next plugin install/sync, are not version-controlled, are not reviewable, and never reach other workspaces that install the plugin.

## Detection (apply BEFORE any read-then-edit on a plugin artifact)

Before reading, creating, or modifying any of the following file types — `rules/**/*.mdc`, `skills/**/SKILL.md` (and siblings), `agents/**/*.md`, `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`, `.cursor-plugin/marketplace.json`, plugin `README.md` — check whether the absolute path contains the substring:

```
/.cursor/plugins/local/
```

If it does, **stop**. You are about to edit the installed mirror, not the source repo.

## Required recovery action

1. Identify the plugin name. It is the directory segment immediately following `/.cursor/plugins/local/`. If unclear, read `~/.cursor/plugins/local/<plugin>/.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` to confirm.
2. Resolve the plugin source repo. For umbraculum's own plugins the source path is `/path/to/umbraculum-toolset/cursor-plugins/<plugin>/`. For third-party plugins, ask the user for the upstream repo path — **do not guess**.
3. Apply the edit in the source repo.
4. Mirror back to the installed location so the active session sees the new behavior immediately (avoid waiting for the next plugin install):

```bash
SRC=/path/to/umbraculum-toolset/cursor-plugins/<plugin>
INST=~/.cursor/plugins/local/<plugin>
cp "$SRC/<relative/path/to/touched/file>" "$INST/<relative/path/to/touched/file>"
```

5. Commit the change from the source repo (the mirror is not a git working tree).

## Anti-pattern

```text
StrReplace path=/home/<user>/.cursor/plugins/local/umbraculum-node-react-cursor-assistant/rules/22-typescript-contracts-runtime-validation.mdc ...
```

Why bad: the substring `/.cursor/plugins/local/` appears in the path → this is the installed mirror, not the source. The next `cursor` plugin sync will silently overwrite it.

## Correct pattern

```text
StrReplace path=/home/<user>/.cursor/plugins/local/umbraculum-node-react-cursor-assistant/rules/22-typescript-contracts-runtime-validation.mdc ...
# then cp the file to ~/.cursor/plugins/local/<same-relative-path> so the active session sees it
# then git add + commit in /path/to/umbraculum-toolset
```

